## Overview

img-settings is a cross-platform desktop application (GUI + CLI) that reads EXIF metadata from photos and stamps a clean watermark with camera settings. It targets WhatsApp-optimised JPEG output (max 2560 px, quality 92). The project is written in Go 1.21+ and uses the Fyne v2 framework for the GUI.

This document outlines the standards that every contributor (human or AI) must follow to keep the codebase consistent, testable, and maintainable.

---

## Technology Stack

### Core

| Component | Technology | Notes |
|-----------|-----------|-------|
| Language | Go 1.21+ | Modules mode, `go.mod` is the source of truth |
| GUI framework | `fyne.io/fyne/v2` v2.6.x | CGO required; Apple-inspired custom theme |
| Graphics rendering | `github.com/fogleman/gg` v1.3.0 | Watermark drawing |
| EXIF parsing | `github.com/rwcarlsen/goexif` | Reads aperture, shutter, ISO, focal length, model |
| Image manipulation | `golang.org/x/image` | Resize (CatmullRom), orientation correction |
| Embedded font | `golang.org/x/image/font/gofont/goregular` | No external font files needed |

### Build & Tooling

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `make` | Primary build orchestrator |
| `go vet` | Static analysis (mandatory in CI) |
| `go test` | Unit testing |
| `fyne` CLI | macOS `.app` bundle packaging |
| `mingw-w64` | Windows cross-compilation from macOS |
| `semantic-release` | Automated versioning and GitHub releases |

### CI/CD

- **GitHub Actions** — CI (`ci.yml`) and release (`release.yml`) workflows
- **Dependabot** — Monthly Go module updates
- **Semantic Release** — Commit-message–driven versioning on `main`

