## Build System

### Makefile Targets

| Target | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `make all` | Build macOS (arm64 + amd64) + Windows + CLI |
| `make macos` | macOS arm64 and amd64 binaries |
| `make windows` | Windows amd64 `.exe` (requires `mingw-w64`) |
| `make cli` | CLI binary (CGO disabled) |
| `make dev` | Fast native dev build |
| `make bundle-macos` | macOS `.app` bundle via Fyne CLI |
| `make clean` | Remove `dist/` and `.syso` files |
| `make fyne-setup` | Install the Fyne CLI tool |

All binaries are emitted to `dist/`.

### Cross-Compilation

| Target | CGO | Compiler variable |
|--------|-----|------------------|
| macOS arm64 | enabled | default Xcode toolchain |
| macOS amd64 | enabled | default Xcode toolchain |
| Windows amd64 | enabled | `CC=x86_64-w64-mingw32-gcc` |
| CLI (any) | disabled | — |

Never enable CGO for the CLI binary — it must remain a single static binary with no external dependencies.

### Version Injection

The current git tag (or `dev` fallback) is injected at link time:

```makefile
VERSION := $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo dev)
LDFLAGS := -s -w -X main.version=$(VERSION)
```

Every binary exposes `var version string` in its `main` package.

